title: Licuala ferruginea
text: Licuala ferruginea is a species of <a href="palm%20tree">palm tree</a> from the <a href="genus">genus</a> "<a href="Licuala">Licuala</a>". It is found in <a href="Singapore">Singapore</a>, including in the <a href="Bukit%20Timah%20Nature%20Reserve">Bukit Timah Nature Reserve</a>. It is also found in <a href="Peninsular%20Malaysia">Peninsular Malaysia</a>. It is a small palm with a short stem. It has between 10 and 13 <a href="leaflet%20%28botany%29">leaflets</a>. The central leaflet is the longest and can grow to up to one meter long. The <a href="flower">flower</a>s have hairy <a href="ovary">ovaries</a>. The fruits are pink when young and black when mature.
